  "market_context": "ETH consolidates into the new day with previous day low swept multiple times forming three drives lower. Price repeatedly fails to displace below the range lows, signaling a potential reversal back into the previous day's range at the 10:00 a.m. new hourly candle.",
  "key_observation": "Three drives into the consolidation low fail to displace lower, and the hourly candle sweeps the lows then closes back inside the range, indicating bullish intent to trade back into the previous day's range.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify consolidation into the new day with previous day low swept multiple times (three drives) and equal highs as the range high.",
    "Note repeated failure to displace lower out of the range, framing it as a consolidation rather than continuation.",
    "Wait for the 10:00 a.m. new hourly candle to sweep the low and close back inside the range, confirming bullish bias.",
    "Drop down to the 5-minute chart and wait for a closure through the series of down-close candles into the relevant point of interest (sweep of lows).",
    "Once 5-minute confirmation occurs, the indicator marks the t-spot where the higher timeframe wick is anticipated to form.",
    "Drop to the 1-minute timeframe and search for an inversion fair value gap within the t-spot zone to trigger entry.",
    "Enter on the retest of the inversion with stop below the swing low, targeting 2R back toward the previous day's range / short-term high."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When price three-drives into a consolidation low without displacement, anticipate a sweep and closure back inside on the new hourly candle. Use 5-minute CISD plus 1-minute inversion entry to trade back into the prior day's range with defined risk.",
